quran[33]{c,v,t}:
  18,99,"And we left some of them to surge on that day over others, and the trumpet will be blown, and we will gather them together"
  18,100,And we will set forth hell on that day before the misbelievers
  18,101,"whose eyes were veiled from my Reminder, and who were unable to hear"
  18,102,"What! did those who misbelieve reckon that they could take my servants for patrons beside me? Verily, we have prepared hell for the misbelievers to alight in"
  18,103,"Say, 'Shall we inform you of those who lose most by their works"
  18,104,"those who erred in their endeavours after the life of this world, and who think they are doing good deeds"
  18,105,"Those who misbelieve in the signs of their Lord and in meeting Him, vain are their works; and we will not give them right weight on the resurrection day"
  18,106,"That is their reward, - hell! for that they misbelieved and took my signs and my apostles as a mockery"
  18,107,"Verily, those who believe and act aright, for them are gardens of Paradise to alight in"
  18,108,"to dwell therein for aye, and they shall crave no change therefrom"
  18,109,"Say, 'Were the sea ink for the words of my Lord, the sea would surely fail before the words of my Lord fail; aye, though we brought as much ink again"
  18,110,"Say, 'I am only a mortal like yourselves; I am inspired that your God is only one God. Then let him who hopes to meet his Lord act righteous acts, and join none in the service of his Lord"
  19,1,H. Z
  19,2,The mention of thy Lord's mercy to His servant Zachariah
  19,3,when he called on his Lord with a secret calling
  19,4,"Said he, 'My Lord! verily, my bones are weak, and my head flares with hoariness; - and I never was unfortunate in my prayers to Thee, my Lord"
  19,5,"But I fear my heirs after me, and my wife is barren; then grant me from Thee a successor"
  19,6,"to be my heir and the heir of the family of Jacob, and make him, my Lord! acceptable"
  19,7,"O Zachariah! verily, we, give thee glad tidings of a son, whose name shall be John. We never made a namesake of his before"
  19,8,"Said he, 'My Lord! how can I have a son, when my wife is barren, and I have reached through old age to decrepitude"
  19,9,"He said, 'Thus says thy Lord, It is easy for Me, for I created thee at first when yet thou wast nothing"
  19,10,"Said he, 'O my Lord! make for me a sign.' He said, 'Thy sign is that thou shalt not speak to men for three nights (though) sound"
  19,11,"Then he went forth unto his people from the chamber, and he made signs to them: 'Celebrate (God's) praises morning and evening"
  19,12,O John! take the Book with strength;' and we gave him judgment when a boy
  19,13,"and grace from us, and purity; and he was pious"
  19,14,"and righteous to his parents, and was not a rebellious tyrant"
  19,15,"So peace upon him the day he was born, and the day he died, and the day he shall be raised up alive"
  19,16,"And mention, in the Book, Mary; when she retired from her family into an eastern place"
  19,17,and she took a veil (to screen herself) from them; and we sent unto her our spirit; and he took for her the semblance of a well-made man
  19,18,"Said she, 'Verily, I take refuge in the Merciful One from thee, if thou art pious"
  19,19,"Said he, 'I am only a messenger of thy Lord to bestow on thee a pure boy"
  19,20,"Said she, 'How can I have a boy when no man has touched me, and when I am no harlot"
  19,21,"He said, 'Thus says thy Lord, It is easy for Me! and we will make him a sign unto man, and a mercy from us; for it is a decided matter"